<div class="block legal">

<p>
Tawala knows that you care about how your personal information is
used and shared, and we take your privacy seriously. Please read the following
to learn more about our privacy policy. By visiting Tawala's web site,
submitting information or using any of our products or services, you
acknowledge that you accept the practices and policies outlined in this Privacy
Policy.
</p>

<br />
<p>
    <b>WHAT DOES THIS PRIVACY POLICY COVER?</b>
    <br />
    This Privacy Policy covers Tawala's treatment of personally
    identifiable information (&quot;Personal Information&quot;) that Tawala gathers
    when you are accessing Tawala's web site and when you use Tawala product or
    services. The types of Personal Information collected may include your full
    name, address, e-mail address, telephone number, and credit card information.
    Also, this Policy covers Tawala's treatment of any Personal Information that
    Tawala's business partners share with Tawala. This policy does not apply to the
    practices of companies that Tawala does not own or control, or to individuals
    that Tawala does not employ or manage.
    Further, this policy does <i>not</i>
    cover the treatment of information that you deploy to Tawala's hosting service
    or collect as part of a private project; please see our <a href="faq">FAQ's</a>
    and our <a href="terms">applicable terms of service</a>
    for more information regarding private deployed
    projects.
</p>

<br />
<p>
    <b>WHAT PERSONAL INFORMATION DOES TAWALA COLLECT?</b>
    <br />
    The information we gather from customers enables us to personalize
    and improve our products and services. We collect the following types of
    information from our customers.
</p>

<br />
<div>
    <b>Personal Information You Provide to Us:</b>
    <br />
    We may receive and store any information you enter on our web site
    or provide to us in any other way. The Personal Information you provide may be
    used for such purposes as responding to your requests for certain products and
    services, customizing the content you see, and communicating with you about
    specials, sales offers, and new products.
</div>
<br />
<div>
    <b>Personal Information Collected Automatically:</b>
    <br />
    <ul>
        <li>
        We may receive and store certain types of information whenever you
        interact with our web site or services. Tawala may choose to automatically
        receive and record information on our server logs from your browser including
        your IP address, Tawala cookie information, your browser and operating system
        configuration and the page you requested.
        </li>

        <li>
        Generally, our service may automatically collect usage
        information, such as the numbers and frequency of visitors to our site and its
        components. Tawala only uses this data in aggregate form, that is, as a
        statistical measure, and not in a manner that would identify you personally.
        This type of aggregate data enables us to figure out how often customers use
        parts of the web site or services so that we can make them appealing to as many
        customers as possible, and improve those services. As part of this use of
        information, we may provide aggregate information to our partners about how our
        customers, collectively, use our site. We share this type of statistical data
        so that our partners also understand how often people use their services and
        our web site, so that they, too, may provide you with an optimal online
        experience.
        </li>

        <li>
        Our product automatically gathers certain information related to
        the usage and effectiveness of our online support services. We only use such
        data in the aggregate, and not in a form that would identify you personally.
        This aggregate data helps us determine how effective support service is, so we
        can improve our service tools and make them as effective as possible.
        </li>
    </ul>
</div>
<br />
<p>
    <b>E-mail Communications:</b>
    <br />
    We may receive a confirmation when you open an e-mail from Tawala
    if your computer supports this type of program. We may also compare our customer list to lists received from
    other companies, in an effort to avoid sending unnecessary messages to our
    customers. 
